article.headline: Old Dominion 63, South Alabama 55
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Valdas Vasylius had 19 points and 12 rebounds and Old Dominion went on a 15-6 run after squandering most of a 12-point second-half lead Saturday night, ralling to beat South Alabama 63-55 in the season opener for both teams. The Monarchs led 44-32 after Drew Williamson's layup with 16:10 to play, then went cold as the Jaguars scored the next 11 points to get within 44-43 with 11:25 left. Arnaud Dahi broke the run with a layup, Vasylius made four free throws and a layup, Isaiah Hunter hit a jumper, Alex Loughton a free throw and Kiah Thomas a layup, giving the Monarchs a 59-49 lead with 4:59 left. South Alabama never got closer than four. Loughton added 11 points for Old Dominion, which shot just 39 percent, missed 11 of 13 3-point shots and 12 of 29 free throws. Mario Jointer lead South Alabama with 14 points and Brandon Gordon had 12.
